治愈4名重症患者，上海用了两大“利器”。
Healing 4 serious patients, Shanghai used two "sharp tools."
澎湃新闻                      。
The news is roaring.
澎湃新闻。
The news is roaring.
有内涵的时政新媒体。
Connotation of the new political media.
澎湃新闻记者 何颖晗 栾晓娜 陈斯斯Play2月22日，上海16例新冠肺炎患者痊愈出院。
Pang journalist Luan Yinghan Chen Si Pai Feb. 22, 16 cases of Newcastle Pneumonia in Shanghai recovered from hospital.
如何救治重症患者，专家沈银忠接受澎湃新闻采访。
How to treat serious patients, expert Shen Yinzhong accepted the news coverage.
澎湃新闻见习记者 邹桥 编辑 顾一帆(00:37)2月22日上午9时30分，在上海市公共卫生临床中心，16例新冠肺炎患者经医护人员精心诊治和护理、专家组评估，认为符合国家卫生健康委最新的新型冠状病毒肺炎确诊病例解除隔离和出院标准，于当日出院。
Peng Pai News Student Journalist Gu Yifan (00: 37) At 9: 30 am on Feb. 22, 16 patients with Newly Coronavirus Pneumonia were discharged from the hospital the same day after intensive medical treatment, nursing and expert group assessment.
值得一提的是，此次出院患者中有4名重症患者。
It is worth mentioning that four of the discharged patients were seriously ill.
2月22日，上海市公共卫生临床中心，上海医疗救治专家组成员、复旦大学附属中山医院感染病科主任胡必杰接受采访。
February 22, Shanghai Public Health Clinical Center, Shanghai Medical Treatment Expert Group, Fudan University affiliated Zhongshan Hospital Infection Director Hu Bijie interview.
澎湃新闻见习记者 邹桥 图据上海医疗救治专家组成员、复旦大学附属中山医院感染病科主任胡必杰透露，这几名重症患者中，有的曾严重缺氧、呼吸衰竭，有的用了机械通气，还有两个用了高流量吸氧。
Some of the seriously ill patients had severe hypoxia, respiratory failure, some used mechanical ventilation and two used high-throughput oxygen, according to Hu Bizjie, a member of the Shanghai Medical Treatment Expert Group and Director of Infection Disease at Zhongshan Hospital, Fudan University.
“两名是65岁以上的老年病人，另外两名分别是47岁和52岁，没有达到老年标准却是重症，我们分析了原因。
"Two elderly patients over the age of 65 and two others aged 47 and 52, respectively, are seriously ill when they do not meet the old-age standard," we analyzed.
”他说，其中一名有糖尿病，另一名有冠心病，之前做过介入治疗。
One of them has diabetes and the other has coronary heart disease, he said, after intervention.
“所以我们一直讲，要特别关注容易发生重症、危重症的病人，早期发现，早期干预，积极处置。
"So we are always talking about paying special attention to the patients who are prone to serious and serious diseases, early detection, early intervention and active treatment.
”胡必杰告诉记者，这几名重症病人，也符合了之前的预判，一种是年纪大的，一种有基础性疾病的。
Mr Hu told reporters that the patients, who were critically ill, also met previous predictions that one was an old, a basic disease.
上海如何救治新冠肺炎重症患者？胡必杰透露，在他们的治疗过程中，一方面是使用抗病毒药物进行治疗，即使用了上海自己的专家分析下来觉得比较好的几个药物；二是严格限制激素使用，即使使用，也是很小剂量很短时间（三天），因此大部分患者都比较好地维护了免疫功能。
How to treat patients with severe pneumonia in Shanghai? Hu revealed that in their treatment, on the one hand, antiviral drugs are used, that is, a few drugs that Shanghai's own experts have analyzed are better, and second, severe restrictions on hormone use, even if used, are very short doses (three days), so most patients maintain immune function relatively well.
此外，还配合了肠道、睡眠、情绪等方面的管理，这些也都是比较关注的问题。
In addition, the management of intestine, sleep, emotion, etc. is also a concern.
上海市公共卫生临床中心医务部主任感染与免疫科主任医师沈银忠进一步表示，对于重症患者的救治，主要是多学科团队的综合诊治和密切配合，包括重症科、呼吸科、ICU、中医等多团队。
Shen Yinzhong, director of infection and immunology department at the Shanghai Public Health Clinical Center, said that the treatment of severe cases was mainly a multi-disciplinary team, including intensive care, respiratory unit, ICU, Chinese medicine and other multi-team.
“这类患者涉及的问题方方面面，如呼吸、心脏等，因此需要多个学科的团队一起努力。
"This kind of patient involves all aspects of the problem, like breathing, the heart, and so on, so it takes a multidisciplinary team to work together.
”沈银忠告诉记者，很多重症患者往往具有基础性疾病，如高血压、糖尿病等，如果能很好地控制好血压、血糖，那么对感染患者的恢复也是有帮助的。
Shen told reporters that many patients with serious illnesses, such as high blood pressure and diabetes, can also help patients recover if their blood pressure and blood sugar are well controlled.
同时，在救治过程中，一些新技术的应用也至关重要，如高流量吸氧、ECMO等。
At the same time, in the treatment process, the application of some new technologies, such as high-volume oxygen absorption, ECMO and so on.
不过，22日出院的重症患者都没有使用ECMO，一般危重症患者可能会需要使用。
However, none of the critically ill patients discharged on the 22nd used ECMO, which is likely to be required for critically ill patients.
那么，对于有基础性疾病的患者来说，新冠肺炎的感染，是否会加重相应病症，并引发并发症？“一个新的疾病，我们对它的认识是不断加深的过程。
So, for people with basic illnesses, does the new crown pneumonia increase the severity of the illness and lead to complications? "" A new disease, we know about it is a growing process.
”沈银忠对此表示，一方面，如果患者有基础疾病，对于新冠肺炎的感染，会有加重的趋势，同等感染的病情，可能比别人更严重；另一方面，如果合并有新冠肺炎的感染，那么对糖尿病、高血压的控制，也可能产生一些不利的影响。
"On the one hand, there is a tendency for patients with basic illnesses to become infected with new crown pneumonia, with the same infection possibly more serious than others, and on the other hand, the control of diabetes mellitus and hypertension may have some negative effects if the infection is combined with pneumonia.
“这进一步证明了，这一类疾病的救治，需要多学科团队的配合。
"This is further evidence that the treatment of this type of disease requires the collaboration of multidisciplinary teams.
”他说。
'he said.
